    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-10-17T10:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-10-17T10:50:00-05:00" n="308"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <head>308. Action Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1" type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d308fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National
                        Security File, Country File, Chile, Vol. V, 8/67–11/68. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-10-17T11:50:00-04:00">October 17, 1968, 11:50 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 480 Program for Chile</item>
                </list>
                <p>The attached memorandum (Tab B)<note n="2" xml:id="d308fn2">Tab B was a
                        memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_GWS1">Gaud</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_FOL1">Freeman</persName> to the President, October 10;
                        attached but not printed.</note> from <persName corresp="#p_FOL1">Orville
                        Freeman</persName>/<persName corresp="#p_GWS1">Bill Gaud</persName>
                    recommends your approval of a $3 million <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 480
                    sales agreement with Chile for corn/grain sorghum and rice. Chile would repay
                    this amount in dollars over a 20-year period, with a 10 percent down
                    payment.</p>
                <p>This <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 480 assistance for Chile is urgently
                    needed because of a severe drought which has caused an emergency shortage of
                    livestock feed. Chile has done quite well in meeting the self-help conditions we
                    set in an earlier agricultural sector loan and <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss>
                    480 agreement.</p>
                <p>The Chilean Governent is feeling particularly isolated after the recent military
                    coup in Peru, as Chilean leaders see themselves completely surrounded by
                    military regimes. President <persName corresp="#p_FME1">Frei</persName> would
                    undoubtedly welcome a sign of US support for his democratic government at this
                    moment.</p>
                <p>Charlie Zwick supports the <persName corresp="#p_FOL1"
                        >Freeman</persName>/<persName corresp="#p_GWS1">Gaud</persName>
                    recommendation (Tab A)<note n="3" xml:id="d308fn3">Tab A was a memorandum from
                        Zwick to the President, October 15; attached but not printed.</note>. I also
                    recommend that you approve the negotiation of this sales agreement with
                    Chile.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Walt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Approve<note n="4" xml:id="d308fn4">This option is checked.
                            Handwritten notations by <persName corresp="#p_BWG1">Bowdler</persName>
                            indicate that Dottie Fredley and <persName corresp="#p_LSW1">Sam
                                Lewis</persName> were informed on October 17 at 4:50 p.m. and 4:55
                            p.m., respectively, and a copy was sent to Fredley on October 18.</note>
                    </p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Disapprove</p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Call me</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
